<package name="perl-Mail-DKIM" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>Signs/verifies Internet mail with DKIM/DomainKey signatures</title>
  <description>This module implements the various components of the DKIM and DomainKeys
message-signing and verifying standards for Internet mail. It currently
tries to implement these specifications:

* RFC4871, for DKIM

* RFC4870, for DomainKeys

The module uses an object-oriented interface. You use one of two different
classes, depending on whether you are signing or verifying a message. To
sign, use the the Mail::DKIM::Signer manpage class. To verify, use the the
Mail::DKIM::Verifier manpage class. Simple, eh?</description>
  <devel project="devel:languages:perl" package="perl-Mail-DKIM"/>
</package>
